<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">About This App</h1>

<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
  The Project Tracker is a lightweight productivity tool built with 
  <strong>Ruby on Rails 7.1.6</strong> running on <strong>Ruby 3.2.2</strong>.  
  It uses Turbo, Tailwind CSS, and a clean MVC architecture to deliver a fast,
  modern experience without unnecessary complexity.
</p>

<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
  This application was developed in a cross‑platform environment using:
</p>

<ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
  <li><strong>Ubuntu (WSL2)</strong> — primary Linux development environment</li>
  <li><strong>Windows 11 + PowerShell</strong> — host OS and terminal access</li>
  <li><strong>Rails 7.1.6</strong> — full MVC framework with RESTful controllers</li>
  <li><strong>Ruby 3.2.2</strong> — application runtime</li>
  <li><strong>Bundler 2.2.33</strong> — dependency management</li>
  <li><strong>Puma 8.x</strong> — Rails application server</li>
  <li><strong>Turbo (Hotwire)</strong> — real‑time UI updates without JavaScript frameworks</li>
  <li><strong>Tailwind CSS 4.x</strong> — utility‑first styling</li>
  <li><strong>PostgreSQL (via pg gem 1.5.x)</strong> — production database</li>
  <li><strong>SQLite3</strong> — development database</li>
  <li><strong>VS Code</strong> — primary editor</li>
  <li><strong>Git + GitHub</strong> — version control and repository hosting</li>
  <li><strong>Railway</strong> — deployment platform with managed Postgres</li>
</ul>

<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
  This application was created by <strong>Matthew Lind</strong> in 2026 as part of a
  professional portfolio demonstrating full‑stack Rails development, UI/UX design,
  and modern web application architecture.
</p>

